---
import DocLayout from '../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
import '../styles/showcase.scss';
---

<DocLayout
  title="Contributing"
  description="Contribute to Viking-UI — extend the kit, fix tokens, ship Web Components, and update the showcase."
>
  <div class="page-inner-wrapper">
    <header class="showcase-page-header">
      <p class="showcase-label">Open source</p>
      <h1 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-xl">Contributing</h1>
      <p class="showcase-text-muted">
        Viking-UI is Apache-2.0 and lives in the DEML monorepo. New shared UI belongs in
        <code>frontend/projects/viking-ui/</code> first — extend the kit, do not fork per-page styles.
        Full guidelines: <a href={`${SITE.github}/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">CONTRIBUTING.md</a>.
      </p>
      <div class="demo-row">
        <viking-button-wc variant="primary" href={SITE.github} target="_blank">View on GitHub</viking-button-wc>
        <viking-button-wc variant="secondary" href="/architecture">Architecture</viking-button-wc>
        <viking-button-wc variant="outline" href="/components">Component gallery</viking-button-wc>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="contribute-steps" aria-labelledby="workflow-heading">
      <h2 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm" id="workflow-heading">Development workflow</h2>

      <article class="contribute-step viking-card">
        <h3 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm">1. Clone and install</h3>
        <p class="showcase-text-muted">
          Fork the repository, install frontend dependencies, and start the docs site locally.
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block-panel is-active contribute-code"><code>git clone {SITE.github}.git
cd deml/frontend && npm ci --legacy-peer-deps
npm run build:viking-ui
cd ../viking-ui-docs && npm ci --legacy-peer-deps
npm run dev</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-step viking-card">
        <h3 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm">2. Understand the architecture</h3>
        <p class="showcase-text-muted">
          Read the <a href="/architecture">architecture guide</a> before adding components. Token changes
          start in <code>_variables.scss</code>. Component logic lives under
          <code>src/lib/</code>. Web Components under <code>src/web/</code>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-step viking-card">
        <h3 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm">3. Add or update a component</h3>
        <ol class="showcase-text-muted contribute-checklist">
          <li>Token-only SCSS in <code>src/styles/</code></li>
          <li>Optional Web Component: <code>{'viking-{name}-wc'}</code> in <code>src/web/</code></li>
          <li>Angular wrapper with signal <code>input()</code> / <code>output()</code></li>
          <li>Export from <code>public-api.ts</code> + <code>viking.manifest.json</code></li>
          <li>Showcase demo in <code>viking-ui-docs/src/lib/component-registry.ts</code></li>
          <li>API reference in <code>component-api.ts</code> when adding new props</li>
        </ol>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-step viking-card">
        <h3 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm">4. Run quality gates</h3>
        <p class="showcase-text-muted">
          Pre-commit enforces theme tokens, accessibility, and lint. From repo root:
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block-panel is-active contribute-code"><code>node scripts/enforce-theme.js
cd frontend && npm run test:viking-ui
cd frontend && npm run check:viking-upstream
uvx pre-commit run --all-files</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-step viking-card">
        <h3 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm">5. Sync static CSS (token changes only)</h3>
        <pre class="code-block-panel is-active contribute-code"><code>npm run build:static-css --prefix viking-ui-docs
python scripts/sync_design_system.py</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article class="contribute-step viking-card">
        <h3 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm">6. Submit a pull request</h3>
        <p class="showcase-text-muted">
          Use conventional commits. Document governance changes in THEME.md and BOOK.md Ch.31 together.
          Include screenshots for UI changes and link related issues.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="showcase-category" aria-labelledby="standards-heading">
      <header class="showcase-category-header">
        <h2 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm" id="standards-heading">Contribution standards</h2>
      </header>
      <ul class="showcase-text-muted contribute-checklist">
        <li>Use <code>--viking-*</code> tokens only — no hardcoded hex in components</li>
        <li>WCAG 2.1 AA: visible focus rings, 44px touch targets, no color-only status</li>
        <li>New shared UI in <code>viking-ui</code> library first, then consume in apps</li>
        <li>Compose form controls through <code>viking-field</code> stacks</li>
        <li>Web Components: Shadow DOM + token styles from <code>src/web/core/</code></li>
        <li>Tests required for charts, forms, icons, and auth surfaces</li>
        <li>Never add Material, Bootstrap, PrimeNG, or other third-party UI kits</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="showcase-category" aria-labelledby="showcase-heading">
      <header class="showcase-category-header">
        <h2 class="showcase-heading showcase-heading-sm" id="showcase-heading">Updating this showcase</h2>
        <p class="showcase-text-muted">
          This Astro site (<code>viking-ui-docs/</code>) is the canonical open-source documentation.
          When you add a component demo:
        </p>
      </header>
      <ul class="showcase-text-muted contribute-checklist">
        <li>Add entry to <code>src/lib/component-registry.ts</code> with preview HTML and 4-framework snippets</li>
        <li>Add API props to <code>src/lib/component-api.ts</code> for documented components</li>
        <li>Verify at <code>npm run dev</code> — check gallery, detail page, and playground if applicable</li>
        <li>Detail pages auto-generate at <code>/components/[slug]</code> from the registry</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</DocLayout>

<style>
  .contribute-steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--viking-space-2);
  }

  .contribute-step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--viking-space-1);
  }

  .contribute-code {
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--viking-space-2);
    background: var(--viking-charcoal-950);
    border-radius: var(--viking-radius);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: var(--viking-font-size-sm);
  }

  .contribute-checklist {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--viking-space-half);
    padding-left: var(--viking-space-3);
  }
</style>
